The ode is placed here 111 order that Hor. may end, as he began (1. 1), by inviting the patronage of Maecenas. The next ode is merely a brief epilogue (cf. Introd. p. xvi) announcing that, with this volume, Hor. brought his lyrical compositions to a close.
